-- PKO Gains Most This Month on PAP Report BGK Won’t Sell Stake
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-04-10T07:30:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/pko-gains-most-this-month-on-pap-report-bgk-won-t-sell-stake.html
PKO Bank Polski SA (PEO) , Poland’s
biggest lender, advanced the most this month after PAP newswire
reported Bank Gospodarstwa Krajowego has no plans to sell its 10
percent in PKO this year.  The shares rose 1.6 percent to 33.42 zloty, the most since
March 30, at 9:12 a.m. in Warsaw.  Bank Gospodarstwa Krajowego, a Polish state-owned bank,
doesn’t intend to sell the  holding  this year, PAP said, citing
Deputy Finance Minister  Dominik Radziwill , the chairman of BGK’s
supervisory board, according to the newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
